<h1>I will explore self-help books on stress</h1>
 <p>Reviewing popular books and methods of stress relief is a step in the right direction.  Exploring options to create a personalized plan will help you begin and stick with your goal.  </p>
<p>Several books on stress have workbooks that guide awareness to stressors and identifying ways to reduce stress thru activities or techniques. There are books that focus on time management and anxiety as well as others that link more directly with the stress of a health condition.   Themes that run through most publications, in print or online, are:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Stop - Become aware and able to track stress</li>
	<li>Breathe - Find breathing techniques to reduce stress that work for you.  Try new ways to actively reduce stress. </li>
	<li>Reflect - Process your thoughts by writing down, recording or talking about how you feel</li>
	<li>Choose - What is the most reasonable way to reduce your stress?</li>
</ul>

